07/06/2004
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- During his visit to Rome on Sunday (6 June), US President George W. Bush said that he has nominated Douglas McElhaney as the next US ambassador to BiH.
The appointment of McElhaney, who previously served as US consul general in Milan, now awaits approval by the US Senate.
McElhaney would succeed Clifford Bond in Sarajevo.
In other news Sunday, the Bosnian Serb government announced that a commission tasked with finding the truth about the Srebrenica massacre would present its report a week late, by 13 June.
Officials said the delay was due to new information that requires processing.
(Dnevni avaz - 07/06/04;
PBS BiH, AFP - 06/06/04)
